    "The regularization strength γ > 0 is set automatically by cross-validation.",
    "The multinomial (MN) judge is an absolute judge designed for predicting categorical scores, such as on the Likert scale.",
    "The Likert score can be viewed as an absolute score or as a ranking among options (Carifio and Perla, 2008).",
    "The MN judge is designed for the former.",
    "Our relative judges in Sections 4.3 and 4.4 are designed for the latter."
